---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
import QuantumStates from '../components/QuantumStates.astro';
import DescartesSection from '../components/DescartesSection.astro';
---

<Layout title="Quantum Mechanics & Consciousness - Philosophy & Physics">
	<main>
		<h1>Quantum Mechanics & <span class="text-gradient">Consciousness</span></h1>
		
		<div class="intro-text">
			<p>
				The intersection of quantum mechanics and consciousness presents one of the most 
				fascinating convergences of physics and philosophy, echoing Descartes' fundamental 
				question about the nature of existence and awareness.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="quote-section">
			<blockquote>
				"Cogito, ergo sum" (I think, therefore I am)
				<cite>- René Descartes</cite>
			</blockquote>
		</div>

		<section class="content-section">
			<h2>Quantum States Visualization</h2>
			<QuantumStates />

			<h2>The Wave Function</h2>
			<div class="formula-container">
				<div class="formula">
					<p>Schrödinger's Wave Equation:</p>
					<div class="equation">
						iℏ ∂Ψ/∂t = ĤΨ
					</div>
					<p class="formula-explanation">
						This fundamental equation describes how quantum states evolve over time, 
						perhaps analogous to how consciousness flows through our experience of reality.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="wave-animation">
				<div class="wave"></div>
				<p class="animation-caption">
					Wave function collapse: The moment of observation, like Descartes' moment of self-awareness
				</p>
			</div>

			<h2>Cartesian Dualism & Quantum Measurement</h2>
			<div class="grid-container">
				<div class="topic">
					<h3>The Observer Effect</h3>
					<p>
						Just as Descartes separated mind from matter, quantum mechanics reveals 
						the inseparable role of the observer in determining reality. The act of 
						measurement fundamentally affects the quantum system being observed.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="topic">
					<h3>Consciousness & Collapse</h3>
					<p>
						The quantum measurement problem raises questions similar to Cartesian 
						skepticism: Does consciousness play a special role in collapsing the 
						wave function? Is awareness fundamental to reality itself?
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2>Modern Perspectives</h2>
			<div class="topic">
				<h3>The Copenhagen Interpretation</h3>
				<div class="formula">
					|Ψ⟩ = Σ cᵢ|ψᵢ⟩
				</div>
				<p>
					The superposition of states before measurement mirrors Descartes' methodological 
					doubt - all possibilities exist until consciousness intervenes through observation.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="topic">
				<h3>Quantum Cognition</h3>
				<p>
					Recent theories propose that quantum processes in microtubules within brain 
					neurons might play a role in consciousness, potentially bridging the gap 
					between physical and mental realms that Descartes identified.
				</p>
				<DescartesSection />
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="navigation">
			<a href="/" class="back-button">← Back to Main Page</a>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		margin: auto;
		padding: 1rem;
		width: 800px;
		max-width: calc(100% - 2rem);
		color: white;
		font-size: 20px;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	h1 {
		font-size: 3.5rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.2;
		text-align: center;
		margin: 1em 0;
	}
	.text-gradient {
		background-image: var(--accent-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-size: 400%;
		background-position: 0%;
	}
	.intro-text {
		margin: 2rem 0;
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		text-align: center;
		max-width: 600px;
		margin-inline: auto;
	}
	.quote-section {
		margin: 3rem 0;
		padding: 2rem;
		background: linear-gradient(rgba(var(--accent-dark), 66%), rgba(var(--accent-dark), 33%));
		border-radius: 8px;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent-light), 25%);
	}
	blockquote {
		font-style: italic;
		text-align: center;
		color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
		margin: 0;
	}
	cite {
		display: block;
		margin-top: 1rem;
		font-size: 0.9em;
	}
	.content-section {
		margin: 4rem 0;
	}
	.grid-container {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
		gap: 2rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}
	.topic {
		padding: 1.5rem;
		background: rgba(var(--accent-dark), 0.2);
		border-radius: 8px;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent-light), 15%);
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	.topic h3 {
		color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
		margin-top: 0;
	}
	h2 {
		text-align: center;
		color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
		margin-top: 3rem;
	}
	.formula-container {
		margin: 2rem 0;
		text-align: center;
	}
	.formula {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		background: rgba(var(--accent-dark), 0.3);
		border-radius: 8px;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent-light), 20%);
	}
	.equation {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		margin: 1rem 0;
		font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;
	}
	.formula-explanation {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		margin-top: 1rem;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
	}
	.wave-animation {
		position: relative;
		height: 100px;
		margin: 3rem 0;
		overflow: hidden;
		background: rgba(var(--accent-dark), 0.2);
		border-radius: 8px;
	}
	.wave {
		position: absolute;
		width: 100%;
		height: 100%;
		background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.2), transparent);
		animation: wave 3s infinite linear;
	}
	@keyframes wave {
		0% {
			transform: translateX(-100%) scaleY(0.5);
		}
		50% {
			transform: translateX(0%) scaleY(1);
		}
		100% {
			transform: translateX(100%) scaleY(0.5);
		}
	}
	.animation-caption {
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		margin-top: 1rem;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
	}
	.navigation {
		text-align: center;
		margin-top: 4rem;
	}
	.back-button {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem;
		background: rgba(var(--accent-dark), 0.5);
		color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
		text-decoration: none;
		border-radius: 4px;
		transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
	}
	.back-button:hover {
		background: rgba(var(--accent-dark), 0.8);
	}
</style>